column5: I just got my sled...wow talk about being able to hit spots you only dreamed of.  I was all over Petrie on the Ottawa River today.  Mobility is key to getting to the spots that are not overfished for sure.  Managed a few nice sized eyes.
Hooking up with you guys to try those big lakes like Rice and Simcoe would be a blast.  I will let you know if I am ever up to see my little sis in Alcona or my son in Belleville.
usually catch alot on that road?
